    <stitle>GENERAL INSTRUMENT ELECTRONIC PROGRAMMABLE SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER - DISASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0803302">
        <title>DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <para>The speedometer/tachometer unit consists of (4) serviceable (replaceable) components: speedometer,
                tachometer, odometer and unit housing which includes the printed circuit board. To disassemble the unit
                to access the components:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove (6) screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803308">Figure 8</hotlnk>), (2) ea. on top and bottom and (1) ea. on each end.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803308" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803308" filename="../figg08/G0803308.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Speedometer/Tachometer Unit Serviceable Components</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. UNIT HOUSING (INCLUDES COVER)</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SPEEDOMETER</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. ODOMETER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. TACHOMETER</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. COVER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift off the face unit place place to access the (3) meters.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The speedometer and tachometer each mount on (4) pins. To remove either gauge, grip the
                    edges of the gauge face plate and lift directly away from the housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the odometer, first remove the speedometer gauge. Disconnect the odometer from
                    the printed circuit at connector J1. Remove (2) screws from back of cluster that retain the odometer
                    and clip.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
